label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 29: Extratto da un libro de razza da cavalli del re Ferrante vechio de Aragona
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Treatise in 84 chapters on the anatomy, medical treatment, physical appearance, breeding, training, and care of horses. The manuscript claims to be an abridgment of an otherwise unknown work by Ferdinand I of Naples, an avid horseman.
        Language: Italian
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: Parchment, i + 47 + i; 1-5⁸ 6⁸(-1); gatherings numbered 1-6 in modern pencil, lower right recto.
        Layout: Written in 19 long lines; frame-ruled in faint red ink.
        Script: Written in a cancellaresca script.
        Decoration: Pen flourishes on either side of title (f. 1r) and some chapter headings; calligraphic initials in left margins at beginning of chapters.
        Binding: Original Venetian morocco over pasteboard, blind- and gilt-tooled.
        Origin: Probably written in Venice, in 1541 (f. 47r).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 29
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5027011 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5027011
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs29.html
